for the first time in a long time, I decided to release a song without a plan, without worrying about pre-saves or viral videos and without telling anyone about it...because I'm releasing this for me and sometimes that's the most important thing! 🤍 #countrymusic

7 years ago, completely out of the blue, I decided to release a song called "When I'm Over You" while I was going through one of the darkest periods of my life. Little did I know that this song would go on to change the trajectory of my career and open doors I never imagined possible. 

I always knew I wanted to revisit this song at some point because it's so special to me, but I was waiting for something to tell me it was the right time. Well...in August 2022, after many years, I ended up crossing paths with the person I wrote this song about. But instead of being consumed by all of the horrible emotions I thought I would be...I felt an overwhelming sense of peace and closure. 

For the longest time I wondered what I'd do when I was finally over him and I guess now I have the answer. This is "When I'm Over You (Piano Version)" featuring my dear friend and co-writer, David Evans on keys...and I hope you love it as much as I do! 🤍 #WhenImOverYou

Happy Birthday Mum! ✨

I know this time of year is never an easy one and you’d rather not acknowledge another trip around the sun, but if anyone is deserving of a celebration, it’s you.

All the “thank you’s” in the world could never be enough to express how grateful I am to have you as a Mum. You’ve made sacrifices throughout your life, for others, that no person should ever have to make and the craziest part is you CHOSE to make them because, for better or worse, you always put others before yourself. 

I am everything I am because of you, and there’s no greater compliment than when people point out our similarities - albeit our differences make us fight like cats and dogs sometimes!! 

You’re my partner in crime, the first person I tell when something goes wrong or goes right, my greatest supporter and my toughest critic. You fought to bring me into this world, and now you’re fighting to stay in it with me. 

Thank you, for everything. 

I can’t wait for even more memories, adventures, pitfalls, challenges and all the in between. No matter what life throws our way, we’ll face it as we always have…together. I LOVE YOU! ❤
